The COVID-19 pandemic has accelerated the adoption of industrial and service robots in various industries to minimize human contact and improve resilience in supply chains.

What are the cost implications of implementing industrial and service robots in a business?
The cost implications of implementing industrial and service robots vary based on factors such as the type of robot, application, customization, and potential return on investment in terms of productivity and efficiency gains.

How does the industrial and service robot market address the ongoing labor shortage in certain industries?
The industrial and service robot market addresses the ongoing labor shortage by automating repetitive and labor-intensive tasks, allowing businesses to redeploy human workers to more skilled and strategic roles.

